# Walkthrough: UA Disambiguation Implementation

I have successfully updated the importer script to handle keyword disambiguation as requested.

## Changes Implemented

I modified [importer_ua_expanded.py](file:///C:/Users/Yorri/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/dnd_ua/importer_ua_expanded.py) to add a normalization step in the [parse_ua_row](file:///C:/Users/Yorri/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/dnd_ua/verify_parsing.py#7-46) function.
The script now:
1.  **Extracts the Year** from the `Date` column.
2.  **Identifies Base Class Updates** using keyword heuristics (e.g., "Revised Ranger", "Mystic class").
3.  **Normalizes Keywords** to the format `Class Name (UA Year)`.

**Example Transformations:**

| Original Content (messy) | Old Concept Name | **New Concept Name** |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| "Full revised **Ranger** class..." | "Full revised Ranger class... (UA)" | **"Ranger (UA 2016)"** |
| "**Mystic class** (10 levels)..." | "Mystic class (10 levels)... (UA)" | **"Mystic (UA 2016)"** |
| "**Artificer class** with Alchemist..." | "Artificer class with Alchemist... (UA)" | **"Artificer (UA 2017)"** |
| "The **Artificer** Revisited" | "The Artificer Revisited (UA)" | **"Artificer (UA 2019)"** |
| "**Wizard (Artificer)**" | "Wizard (Artificer) (UA)" | **"Artificer (UA 2015)"** |

